## Summary of All Affected Files

| File | Bug | Issue |
|------|-----|-------|
| [multi_provider.py](file:///Users/mac/Desktop/phhh/backend/app/services/multi_provider.py) | Bug 1 | [deep_research](file:///Users/mac/Desktop/phhh/backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/research.py#30-69) priority routes to Mistral first |
| [deep_research.py](file:///Users/mac/Desktop/phhh/backend/app/services/deep_research.py) | Bug 1 | Silent search tool failures, token limits |
| [research.py](file:///Users/mac/Desktop/phhh/backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/research.py) | Bug 2 | No database persistence, broken `db` injection |
| [useChatStreaming.ts](file:///Users/mac/Desktop/phhh/frontend/src/hooks/useChatStreaming.ts) | Bug 2 | Creates local-only messages with no backend save |

## Recommended Investigation Order

1. **Verify API key status** — Check if `TAVILY_API_KEY`, `SERP_API_KEY`, and `SERPER_API_KEY` are set and valid in the environment. If these are all missing/expired, the research tools return nothing and the LLM generates from base knowledge only.
2. **Check server logs** — Look for `✅ Selected mistral with model mistral-large-latest` log lines during Deep Research. This confirms the wrong provider is being selected.
3. **Verify the [DeepResearchService()](file:///Users/mac/Desktop/phhh/backend/app/services/deep_research.py#511-1356) instantiation** — The missing `db` argument should be causing a runtime error. Check if there's error suppression happening.
